HEADWORD: Gallinae
<hw>Gal*li"nae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it></plu> <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>gallina</ets> a hen,
<ets>gallus</ets> a cock.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
birds, including the common domestic fowls, pheasants, grouse, quails,
and allied forms; -- sometimes called
<altname><ord>Rasores</ord></altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

